## Visual design language (from "Pages that matter")

**Use this language for all new UI, including onboarding.** Onboarding wireframes (`1-3`) define *flow and copy placeholders* only — apply the polished patterns below.

### Palette (Late Afternoon Beach)

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|--------|
| Coral primary | `#F9B3A6` | Primary buttons, match screen bg, active pager dot |
| Coral brand | `#FBA797` | "After Class" wordmark on white screens |
| White | `#FFFFFF` | Screen bg, secondary buttons, badges, bottom sheet |
| Inactive gray | `#D9D9D9` | Inactive pager dots, sheet grab handle |
| Black | `#000000` | Headlines, button labels on coral/white |
| Surface tint | `rgba(249,179,166,0.7)` | Discovery card backdrop |

CSS variables: `ui/tokens.css`. Assets: `ui/assets/logo-sun.png`, `ui/assets/onboarding-hero.png`.

### Typography

Uses **SF Pro** via the iOS system font stack (`-apple-system` / system default in RN).

| Role | Style | Size | Weight |
|------|-------|------|--------|
| Brand wordmark | Title 3 | 20px | Semibold (600) |
| Hero headline | Large Title | 34px | Bold (700) |
| Section title | Title 1 | 28px | Bold (700) |
| Body / tagline | Body | 17px | Regular (400) |
| Button label | Headline | 17px | Semibold (600) |
| Helper / subhead | Subhead | 15px | Regular (400) |

CSS tokens: `ui/tokens.css`. Mobile scale: `mobile/constants/typography.ts`.

### Recurring components

1. **App header** — centered logo (35×35 sun) + "After Class" in `#FBA797`; ~34px from top.
2. **Primary button** — pill (`border-radius: 48px`), 346×62px, coral fill, black Inter Medium 14px label. Bottom-anchored with ~28px side inset.
3. **Secondary button** — same pill shape, white fill, black label (e.g. match CTA "See where you'll meet!").
4. **Pager dots** — 12×12 circles; active `#F9B3A6`, inactive `#D9D9D9`; centered above primary button.
5. **Hero illustration** — large centered 3D/character art (~366px) below header on welcome.
6. **School badge** — white pill, map pin icon + school name (discovery only).
7. **Floating tab bar** — white pill 265×50, shadow, coral icons (Heart / Home / Person).
8. **Bottom sheet** — white panel, 19px top radius, gray grab handle (meetup screen).

### Screen backgrounds

- **Default:** white (`Welcome`, `Main`, `Mapepd date`)
- **Celebration:** full coral fill (`Matched Page`) with white text + white CTA

### Onboarding wireframes → apply polished template

Wireframe section `1-3` — implement with **Welcome page** (`11-37`) as the layout template:

| Wireframe | node-id | Headline (wireframe) | Primary CTA | Notes |
|-----------|---------|----------------------|-------------|-------|
| Welcome 1 | `1-6` | "Welcome, Insert Text Here!" | Next | Carousel slide 1 — replace placeholder with product copy |
| Welcome 2 | `4-13` | "Hot Singles in your Area…" | Next | Slide 2 |
| Welcome 3 | `4-22` | "Start Meeting After Class!" | Get Started | Final carousel → routes to Auth |
| Auth Page | `4-36` | "Start Meeting After Class!" | Sign in + Create Account | Two stacked primary-style buttons |
| Sign In | `4-60` | "Welcome Back" | Sign in + OAuth stack | Back arrow; email/password fields; "or" divider; Google / Apple / Number |

**Onboarding content rules:**
- Reuse tagline on every carousel slide: *"Match with verified students. We plan the daytime date. You just show up."*
- 3-slide carousel with pager dots (same as Welcome page).
- Do **not** use wireframe gray boxes or lorem ipsum in code — use PRD-aligned copy.
- Sign In wireframe includes Apple/Number — confirm against PRD (MVP: `.edu` + Google OAuth only); hide or defer non-MVP providers unless user approves.

